place.name: WOOLLEY
place.gazetteerText: WOOLLEY, a parish in Bath district, Somerset; 2¾ miles N of Bath r. station. Post town, Bath. Acres, 365. Real property, £885. Pop., 71. Houses, 14. The living is a rectory, annexed to Bathwick. The church is plain. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
